description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about delivering the very best patient care and working as part of a great team, this could be just the job for you! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a key team member, our patient flow co-ordinator will need to be able to provide support to our patients, their families and the ward teams related to safe, timely discharge, ensuring a smooth transition from the Acute hospital setting back into the community. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will work collaboratively with our patients and their families, Medical colleagues, ward teams, outside agencies and local authorities to ensure a &#39;joined up&#39; approach to caring for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires an organised individual who can work independently and as part of a team, ensuring prompt discharge planning, identifying whether a patient has simple or complex needs; coordinating the discharge or transfer process; and in partnership with the ward team, patients and carers set an expected date of discharge to aim towards. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate must have excellent communication skills. Experience in the use of hospital I.T. systems would be desirable though not essential as full training and support would be given. The ability to input and provide accurate data and reports would also be desirable. If you feel you have the qualities required to fulfil this role and you are dedicated to high quality, patient centred care we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
